\section{China 1960 Beijing Railway Station}

The Beijing Railway Station was one of the largest construction projects in mainland China during that time with modern facilities and it was also China's first large modern railway terminal. A the time of completion, the station has a twelve tracks and six railway platforms with canopies attached to them. 


